.lk/directory_of_members/ViewMember.do?memID=267|title=T.B. EKANAYAKE|work=Directory of Members|publisher=[[Parliament of Sri Lanka]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101013020114/http://www.parliament.lk/directory_of_members/ViewMember.do?memID=267|archivedate=13 October 2010}}, Deputy Minister Education (2010\u20132015)\n* [[Sarath Ekanayake]] \u2013 7th and current Chief Minister of the Central Province of Sri Lanka<ref>[http://www.cpcouncil.net/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=50&Itemid=53 Sri Lankan Central Province Council Website]</ref>\n* [[Nandimithra Ekanayake]] \u2013 Member of Parliament (1989\u20132015); Chief Minister of Central Province (1999\u20132000); Minister of Environmental and Forest Resources (1996\u20131999)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2011/12/29/fea04.asp|title=Features |work= Daily News |access-date=3 March 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Niluka Ekanayake]] \u2013 [[List of Governors of Central Province|Governor of Central Province]] (2016\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/archive/20061224/issues.htm|title=When the President saw stars|newspaper=[[The Sunday Leader]]|date=24 December 2006|accessdate=17 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adaderana.lk/news/34584/niluka-ekanayake-sworn-in-as-cp-governor|title=Niluka Ekanayake sworn in as CP Governor|publisher=[[Ada Derana]]|date=17 March 2016|accessdate=17 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[E. M. R. B. Ekanayake]] (?-1962), Member of Parliament \u2013 [[Mawatagama Electoral District|Mawatagama]] (1960)\n* [[S. B. Ekanayake]] (1906\u20131977), Member of Parliament \u2013 [[Soranatota Electoral District|Soranatota]] (1960\u20131965)\n* [[Herath Ekanayake]] (1927\u20131971), Member of Parliament \u2013 [[Mawatagama Electoral District|Mawatagama]] (1965\u20131970)\n\n==Ellawala==\n* [[William Ellawala]], Member, Ceylon Legislative Council\n**William Ellawala Jnr\n***[[Richard Stephen Ellawala]], Basnayake Nilame, Saparagamuwa