ewa Hulangamuwa]] (1955\u20132013), Councillor, Kandy Municipal Council<ref>[http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=70844 President pays respects]. The Island. Retrieved 20 January 2013.</ref>\n*** Devika Mediwake + [[Neranjan Wijeyeratne]] (1956\u2013 )\n(also related to Ratwatte)\n\n==Gunasekara (Heiyantuduwa, Biyagama)==\n*[[Tudor Gunasekara]] \u2013 former Member of Parliament for Mahara,<ref>\n[http://elections.gov.lk/web/wp-content/uploads/election-results/parliamentary-elections/general-election-1977.pdf 1977 Parliamentary Elections Results]. Official Website, Department of Elections, Sri Lanka.</ref> former District Minister for Gampaha, former Sri Lanka ambassador to Poland, Bulgaria, Romania, and Hungary\n**[[Anuradha Dullewe Wijeyeratne]] \u2013 former Councillor of Sabaragamuwa Provincial Council, Ex-Acting Diyawadana Nilame of Sri Dalada Maligawa, Kandy (son-in-law of Tudor Gunasekara)\n\n==Gunasekara (Udugampola, Minuwangoda)==\n* [[Bennet Gunasekera]] \u2013 Member of Parliament for Minuwangoda from 1977 to 1988 \n** [[Mahen Gunasekera]]  \u2013 Minister for Legal Reforms and Prison Affairs \u2013 Member of Parliament for Gampaha District (1989\u20131994)\n\n==Gunawardena (Boralugoda Ralahamy)==\nRef:<ref>{{cite web|title=Family #3069 Gunawardena|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~lkawgw/gen3069.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090720115226/http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~lkawgw/gen3069.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2009-07-20|work=Sri Lankan Sinhalese Family Genealogy|publisher=rootsweb}}</ref>\n* Don Jacolis Rupasinghe Gunawardena (1879\u20131947) + Leonora\n** [[Philip Gunawardena]] (1901\u20131972), Government Minister, Member of Parliament, Member of State Council The 'Father of Socialism in Sri Lanka',<ref name=Ervin>Charles Wesley Ervin, ''Tomorrow is Ours:the Trotskyist Movement in India and Ceylon, 1935\u201348'', Colombo: Social Scientists Association, 2006</ref> first p