0-day programme, Harshana Rajakaruna, parliamentary general election, UNP Provincial Councilor]</ref>Businessmen<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.srilankalive.com/current-affairs/hon-harshana-rajakaruna/ |title=Hon. Harshana Rajakaruna |access-date=19 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215213441/http://www.srilankalive.com/current-affairs/hon-harshana-rajakaruna/ |archive-date=15 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==[[Rajapaksa family|Rajapaksa]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Family #3086 Rajapaksa|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~lkawgw/gen3086.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090112215924/http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~lkawgw/gen3086.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2009-01-12|work=Sri Lankan Sinhalese Family Genealogy|publisher=rootsweb}}</ref>==\n\n* Don David Rajapaksa, [[Vidane Arachchi]]\n** [[D. M. Rajapaksa|Don M Rajapaksa]], Member of State Council, Senator<ref>[http://www.sundaytimes.lk/111106/News/nws_23.html D.A. Rajapaksa- the pulse of Ruhuna]</ref>\n*** [[Lakshman Rajapaksa]], Member of Parliament<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slelections.gov.lk/web/images/pdf/general-election-results/elections1947-1988.pdf|title=Result of Parliamentary By Election 1976|publisher=Department of Elections, Sri Lanka|accessdate=17 May 2017}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*** [[George Rajapaksa]], Government Minister, Member of Parliament<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slelections.gov.lk/web/images/pdf/general-election-results/parliamentary-general-election-1960-07-20.pdf|title=Result of Parliamentary General Election 20 July 1960|publisher=Department of Elections, Sri Lanka|accessdate=21 June 2017}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://203.94.72.22/circulars1/40-ministry/ministry/43-ministers-and-deputy-ministers.html|title=List of Ministers and Deputy Ministers \u2013 Ministry of Finance and Planning|publishe