ial Website of SL Parliament]</ref>\n** [[Imthiaz Bakeer Markar]], (8 August 1953 ) Government Minister, Member of Parliament<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.lk/component/members/viewMember/145?Itemid=206|title=Imthiaz Bakeer Markar|publisher=Parliament of Sri Lanka|accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2014/11/09/pol04.asp |title=UNP is not against raising loans for development \u2013 Imthiaz Bakeer Markar  |access-date=18 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809001004/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2014/11/09/pol04.asp |archive-date=9 August 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Bulankulame==\n* [[P. B. Bulankulame|Punchi Banda Bulankulame Dissawe]],(12 December 1890 \u2013 17 December 1958) Member of the State Council (1936), Member, House of Representatives, Parliamentary Secretary (Agriculture and Lands), Minister of Lands and Land Development<ref>[http://www.atimes.com/ind-pak/CK10Df03.html   Sri Lanka: The Untold Story]</ref><ref>[http://www.island.lk/2005/04/24/features3.html The battle of the Gulliver and the Lilliputian]</ref><ref>[http://sundaytimes.lk/070923/FunDay/heritage.html First cabinet had only 14 ministers]</ref><ref>[http://www.island.lk/2009/05/17/features4.html Late Deshamanya E. L. B. Hurulle]</ref> \n(Maternal Uncle of Edwin Loku Bandara Hurulle and Granduncle of Themiya Loku Bandara Hurulle)\n**[[Deshamanya]] [[E. L. B. Hurulle|Edwin Loku Bandara Hurulle]], (19 January 1919 \u2013 6 April 2009), Member, House of Representatives, Member of Parliament, Government Minister, Governor, Central Province, High Commissioner in Australia, Governor, North Central Province<ref>[http://www.island.lk/2009/05/17/features4.html Deshamanya E. L. B. Hurulle]. The Island, Retrieved on 17 May 2009.</ref><ref>[http://www.sundaytimes.lk/090503/Plus/sundaytimesplus_09.html In victory or defeat he was the gentleman politician]. The Sunday Times, Retrieved on 3 May 2009.</ref> (Nephew of P.B