ntsun= 33\n|Nov percentsun= 32\n|Dec percentsun= 29\n|source 1 = Worldwide Bioclimatic Classification System<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalbioclimatics.org/station/so-trist.htm|title=South Africa: Tristan Da Cunha|date=March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150426191925/http://www.globalbioclimatics.org/station/so-trist.htm#|archive-date=26 April 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|source 2 = Climate and Temperature<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.climatetemp.info/tristan-da-cunha/ |title=Tristan Da Cunha Climate Guide to the Average Weather & Temperatures with Graphs Elucidating Sunshine and Rainfall Data & Information about Wind Speeds & Humidity |date=March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111117211803/http://www.climatetemp.info/tristan-da-cunha/ |archivedate=17 November 2011 }}</ref><ref>http://www.tristandc.com/wildclimate.php</ref>\n\n|date=August 2010\n}}\n\n{{climate chart|Edinburgh of the Seven Seas\n|16|20|93\n|17|21|113\n|16|20|121\n|15|18|129\n|13|17|155\n|11|15|160\n|11|14|160\n|10|14|175\n|10|14|169\n|11|15|151\n|13|17|128\n|15|19|127\n|float=right\n|source=[http://www.climatetemp.info/tristan-da-cunha/ Climate and Temperature Information]\n}}\n\n==Transport==\nThere is one road, M1, which connects the town with Patches and is used by the few private cars on the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/visitsexcursions.php|title=Tristan da Cunha Visitor Excursions|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref> Paved paths provide walking access to buildings around town. A bus service called Potato Patches Flier (using a 24-seat Isuzu mini school bus from South Africa<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristantimes.com/art_4512_56_8_1.html|title=The Tristan Times Newspaper \u2013 News from Tristan da Cunha|accessdate=30 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031101436/http://www.tristantimes.com/art_4512_56_8_1.html|archive-date=31 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>) is available to pensioners in town to travel to places around the island.<ref name=\"tristandc.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/newstransport.php|title=Tristan da Cunha Land Transport News|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nAll motor vehicles on the island have Tristan da Cunha plates consisting of letters TDC and 2 or 3 numbers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olavsplates.com/tristan_da_cunha_abroad.html|title=Olav's Tristanian number plates \u2013 Photographed in Tristan da Cunha|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe town has a small harbour with berths accessible by small vessels only.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Edinburgh-Tristan.jpg|\nFile:Edinburgh of the Seven Seas 01.jpg|\nFile:Edinburgh of the Seven Seas 03.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n==Art==\nGraphic artist [[Rolf Weijburg]] produced an etch of Edinburgh of the Seven Seas<ref>http://www.weijburg.nl/portofolio/etsen/116v.jpg </ref> and other places on the island of [[Tristan da Cunha]].<ref>Rolf Weijburg\u2019s website: http://www.weijburg.nl</ref>\n\n==Local government==\nThe island's local affairs are managed by the Island Council, a 14-member administration that meets six times a year and is elected every three years.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://capital.osd.wednet.edu/media/capital/library/pdf/tristan_da_cunha.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140114222251/http://capital.osd.wednet.edu/media/capital/library/pdf/tristan_da_cunha.pdf |archive-date=14 January 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Government services==\nThe town is home to the island's emergency services, which comprise one ambulance (a [[Toyota Hilux]] operated by Camogli Hospital), one fire engine (a [[Land Rover Defender]] with a small ladder) and one police car ([[Land Rover Series]]).<ref name=\"tristandc.com\"/>\n\nThe town administration also has a vehicle for official use.<ref name=\"tristandc.com\"/>\n\n==Places of interest and attractions==\nMost buildings in town are single story, with the largest being the factory and the tallest being St Joseph's Church.\n\n* St Mary's Anglican Church \u2013 built 1923<ref name=\"tristandc.com1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/churches.php|title=Tristan Churches|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n* [[St. Joseph Church, Edinburgh of the Seven Seas|St. Joseph Catholic Church]] \u2013 built 1995\u201396 and replaced earlier church from 1983<ref name=\"tristandc.com1\"/>\n* St Mary's School \u2013 built 1975<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/school.php|title=Tristan School|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n* Camogli Hospital \u2013 built in 1971 to replace Station Hospital (c. 1940s)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/hospital.php|title=Camogli Hospital Tristan da Cunha|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n* Calshot Harbour \u2013 built 1967<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/harbour.php|title=Tristan da Cunha's Calshot Harbour|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n* Prince Philip Hall and the Albatross Bar\n* Tristan Thatched House Museum\n* Agriculture Department warehouse\n* Tristan Island Store \u2013 only supermarket on the island<ref name=\"tristandc.com2\">http://www.tristandc.com/shops.php</ref>\n* Tristan Post Office, Tourism Centre and Caf\u00e9 da Cunha \u2013 opened 2009<ref name=\"tristandc.com2\"/>\n* Administration Building \u2013 home to Island Council\n* Crayfish Canning Factory \u2013 built 1963<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristandc.com/economyfishing.php|title=Tristan Fishing|publisher=|accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref>\n* Park 61 \u2013 volcanic park site\n\n==Notable people== \n*[[Conrad Glass]], police officer\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tristandc.com/settlement.php Description of the settlement]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170106201949/http://members.virtualtourist.com/m/28be5/1075/9/ Tourism Information (Archived)]\n\n